- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of MASs in providing self-organising features in digital ecosystems.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses distributed evolutionary computing as a technology that can contribute to self-organising features in digital ecosystems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses Service-Oriented Architectures (SOAs) as a technology that can contribute to self-organising features in digital ecosystems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the potential for exploiting the self-organising properties of biological ecosystems in digital ecosystems, which can be seen as an application of AI.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of robust, scalable self-organising architectures, which can be seen as a control problem.
